<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="420" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1558,2016]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,335,1739,1763]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is an adjective taken from the South American native language Tupi and means “small”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="420" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1558,2016]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,323,1810,1835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[332,485,1811,1835]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Breda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,485,1811,1835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">Breda nanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,586,1811,1835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[494,586,1811,1835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the other species of the genus by having a short and straight tibial apophysis, distally slender (
<figureCitation box="[527,610,1847,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 75" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1272,1295]" captionTargetBox="[156,1417,555,1240]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,555,1251]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 75. Breda nanica sp. nov. 73 male, dorsal view; 74 left male palp, ventral view; 75 ventroretrolateral view. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222778/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="420">
Fig. 
<number box="[579,610,1847,1871]" pageId="19" pageNumber="420" value="75.0">75</number>
</figureCitation>
), and by the absence of white scales on the borders of the carapace.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
